messages.message: hey is anyone else having trouble with `webpack`? None of my frontend changes are being reflected on my crafting sandbox, I even tried creating a new `ibdev` sandbox and I’m having the same issue
@danny.lan which of your sandboxes are you seeing this issue with?
i’m trying on dannylan3 (https://instabase.sandboxes.site/sandboxes/dannylan3) right now

gotcha gotcha! fwict it looks like webpack is disabled on that host (the output of these logs (https://instabase.sandboxes.site/logviewx/instabase/dannylan3/dev/daemon/webpack%40instabase) is demonstrating a check against an environment variable `WEBPACK_ENABLED`, which isn't set when inspecting your command line with e.g. `printenv | sort | grep -i enabled`)

I'm running `workspace service enable webpack` now to turn it on, if that passes you should be good to go!
nice it seems to be working now, thanks Sean!

excellent!! everything ran as expected from the command line too, so hopefully you're all good -- let me know if that doesn't seem to be the case and I'd be happy to help unblock :slightly_smiling_face:
@sean.donohoe I think I'm running into something similar? It's running something but when I try to navigate to almost any page outside of the home page, it gives an error loading webpack bundles:
@Weiming Wu is this for the bug bash sandbox you were getting set up?
merp nvm, I see the name in the URL :sweat_smile: taking a look now
any chance your browser cached some old web artifacts? I'm not able to repro from my own browser (watched the console for login, navigation to build, and navigation to converse)
oh good haha, I was half talking out my butt, I am absolutely pathetic when it comes to front end :joy:
